            'autor' => 'Rafael Ogrim',
            'texto1' => 'Battlefield 1 marks the debut of the series of Electronic Arts shooters at the time of the First World War, though it is told in a more "imaginative" way. The title goes to PS4, Xbox One and PC on October 21 and was one of the games available to play at E3 2016. Only the multiplayer of Battlefield 1 was available to play at E3 2016. The title will have a full campaign mode and with many cinematic moments, but the idea of ​​testing at the fair was to present the main course, which is the online mode, simulated on-site with a large network for participants.', //1° paragrafos,
            'texto2' => 'Huge departure, say by the way. It\'s not every day that we see a battlefield in video games with 64 people, with so many explosions, tense moments and shots everywhere. At first everything seemed a little confused, but soon found ourselves, invading the opponent scene with all our firepower on the Allied side - the only battle was available from the British against the Germans. Before entering, however, we note that the Battlefield 1 classes have not changed much, although this is good news, and despite being in a different scenario from the others. Still no official translation into Portuguese, the game offered us Assault positions, Medic, Support and Scout, each with their duties in the field. Support choose mainly to aim at the enemies across the map, and also to help friends to leave items along the way, such as ammunition.', //2° paragrafos,
            'texto3' => 'One of the first changes is that now the player does not return to the field surrounded by enemies. When you died and returned to the game, the odds appear next to a friend who was already full of opponents around were great. This problem no longer occurs, a relief for those who hoped for fairer matches, at least these minimum details. But let the struggle itself: it is gigantic, impressing even. Battlefield 1 takes a different artistic direction of similar, like Call of Duty, and cherishes a little more realism. Virtually everything around is destructible and the sound effects are top notch. The controls in seemed well suited and worthy of a game in the series, at least in control of Xbox One, platform we tested.', //3° paragrafos,
            'texto4' => 'One of the highlights of the match is a chance to reverse her decision. With our team lost, we received reinforcements armed vehicles and other benefits that came in handy - although they have not been sufficient to define our victory. Vehicles vary: are tanks, planes and even a huge armed airship in every corner, depending on your military strength and departure. The important thing is that thanks to this kind of addition, the multiplayer of Battlefield 1 ceases to be just an online mode to be the main experience we can expect from this type of game. EA is really making a difference in the series with this new chapter, and the DICE studio is using the lessons learned from the poor reception of Battlefield Hardline and also good knowledge from Star Wars: Battlefront - both keep some similarities to 1.',
