            'resumo' => 'PlayStation VR impressed with the realism of Resident Evil 7',
            'autor' => 'Rafael Ogrim',
            'texto1' => 'The PlayStation VR is the new bet of Sony in the world of virtual reality. He arrives on October 13 for $ 399, cheaper than its competitor, the Oculus Rift. We tested it during the demo of Resident Evil 7 at E3 2016, the new game that promises to rescue the essence of terror in the series. Check out our test.', //1° paragrafos,
            'texto2' => 'The virtual reality glasses from Sony is lightweight and fits easily to the face shape. It has adjustments on the top to adjust the shape of the head and another on the front to adjust the distance from the display to the eye, which is great for those who wear eyeglasses. The weight is evenly distributed. The design is simple, beautiful and has blue lights that guarantee you a charm more.', //2° paragrafos,
            'texto3' => 'We tested the PlayStation VR along with a demo of the new Resident Evil 7 in the first person. Experience with virtual reality glasses is totally immersive and realism of the scenarios is the first detail that impresses. The objects really "jump" of the screen and the textures give dimension to rooms and dark corridors. The first few minutes exploring the environments and items immediately surprised. When we think of virtual reality and games, remember games with simpler visual, which are still experimenting and creating on this new technology. But the horror genre has arrived at other levels when combined with virtual reality.', //3° paragrafos,
            'texto4' => 'The new footprint Resident Evil 7 combines with the experience and intensifies all major elements of the genre. If you walk through the halls it was scary, imagine see shadows and hear strange noises when you have the feeling of being in that environment, within the game itself. It closely resembles the demo P.T., who announced already canceled Silent Hills. Only twice realism and scares, of course. Virtual reality technology has the potential to redefine how we see the games, and PlayStation VR is a great start to the games from Sony. The price is still steep for Brazilians but, with the popularization of this genre, we may have prices and a wider range of products. Still, he manages to show how technology is increasingly refining and turning games into even more interactive experiences.', //4° paragrafos,
